\par The counting is a bit more complicated when Black captures White's three stones with 1.
\par
\par 3 captured stones plus the points at Xs makes 8 points.
\par
\par Therefore \b B\b0  in the\b  main diagram\b0  is \cf1\b gote\cf0\b0  1+8=\cf1\b 9 points\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par \b A\b0  is one point bigger than \b B\b0 . The correct answer was \cf2 1)\cf0 .
\par }
